snippet.textDisplay:
please, PLEASE DON'T cancel FaceID in the notchless phone. It's so much more practical than TouchID and simply better. And yes, I've also tested underscreen-fingerprint readers and they are so damn inferior to FaceID. Please keep FaceID, because I really want the notchless iPhone to happen, but TouchID would be a KO for the phone in my eyes and I don't want this to happen.
And yes, both together would be dope for security, but it would still eliminate every advantage FaceID gives you, so no, I don't like that either. It would be really cool though if you could adjust that in the settings and say that the phone unlocks if only one is true, so that you can use either TouchID OR FaceID
